      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "China's claims in the South China Sea, represented by the \"Nine-Dash Line,\" are not recognized by international law. In 2016, the Permanent Court of Arbitration in The Hague ruled against China's expansive maritime claims, stating they violated the United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea (UNCLOS). Despite the ruling, China has refused to acknowledge it, arguing that the arbitration process was biased and not legally binding. This refusal to comply with international law has led to increased tensions and conflicts in the region, as China continues to assert its claims through militarization and aggressive actions. The situation is a clear violation of international law and undermines the rule-based international order.",
      "source": "target",
